content: This is a great app for beginner runners, slowly easing you into running. The only thing that let's the app down is having to change your guide, telling you the guide you chose is no longer available. Apart from this, I would rate the couch to 5k app all day long 😊
Follow every step - it works
Brilliant
Easy to use app, encouraging helps you to maintain the discipline to keep going
Good easy instructions.
Good 9 week program, but occasionally crashes midway through a run which is very annoying

It's good except as others have reviewed, it does keep stopping. I'm going to try going into airplane mode next time to see if it's notifications or emails that are somehow making it stop. Love the way Sarah Milligan keeps telling me how well I'm doing (I tell her she's killing me!) and is now calling me "Flower"!
Brilliant - turning a non running 51 slightly chubby bloke into a slightly less chubby runner!! Highly recommended. 😁

This is the 3rd time I've started couch to 5k as I've needed to stop after a while due to personal circumstances - I rave about this to everyone... YOUR FITNESS IS IRRELEVANT! anyone can do it, honestly it's fantastic. & the fact it makes it so achievable gives you such a feel good vibe. I've completed this before at 17 stone with no previous exercise. Try it!
I found this app very motivational for me.( I am a fit 65) Would have liked some music in the background too.
Only just started but getting along fine
Gr8 app. Love Michael Johnson's voice. Good incremental jumps in distance and encourages a do-able speed.
Great to run to got me running first time in my life
Excellent.
Easy to use and almost seamlessly builds up to 30 mins running.
This helped me a lot
Just love it
Excellent
I couldn't run for a bus. Now I can run (albeit quite slow ) for 30 minutes didnt get to 5k though. The app works .
Easy to use hoping it improves my running
Amazing cannot fault it
This is brilliant!! I did this after having no running experience. If you're someone who wants to start running but isnt sure where to start this is the app for you 😁
Easy to follow.
Great couching tool. I'm 56, not very active and its got me enjoying exercise. For now anyway. Let's see what happens.
Brilliant, easy to use

I've tried running before and never been able to make it into a habit. I'm only on week 2 of this but I'm waking up wanting to go for a run. The coach is really useful and it's great to be able to play music at the same time. Edit: I stuck at it! It took me a bit longer than the 9 weeks but I got there - and it felt good!
Very kind !

The principle is good but I'm now at the end of week 5 and giving up on this app. The app has crashed on me the past 5 or 6 times I've been out for a run which becomes frustrating as you lose your position in your session. It has worked to get me off the couch and I am covering 5k but not running the full 5k yet. The bugs need to be addressed as this is a great app when it works.
Hard but fair
I've used this app a number of times when I want to get my running mojo and confidence back. I think it's great for new and returning runners
Nice to have some encouragement and a goal to work to.

Found it really useful, encouraging to get me running again. Having the voice of another human urging you on certainly helped me get to 5K goal. Will find a way to continue using it for my weekly runs. It's a very good app if you want to start running.
Useful, keeps me motivated. I'm not a runner. I like Michael Johnson's voice.

What a fantastic app. From finding 1 minute running at the beginning of the app extremely hard to completing 30 minutes non stop by the end is such a great feeling. Michael Johnson was a great motivator. Thank you .
A great help for getting me off the couch on the road to wellness.
Great way to restart running.
It's hard for me being super overweight but it's easy to follow and get on with. You just need will power
Absolutely amazing feeling great 👍
Positive, really enjoying using the app. Thanks
Brilliant app!!! Love gentle start to getting me to start loving running
Really good app. Very motivating
Love it !!
Excellent!!! Would recommend to anyone.
Great so far
Fantastic
Very useful app Michael Johnson coaches really well it makes you feel at ease, if only the body could match the app. Very highly recommend it.

Horrendous app. Completed first run and the app shut itself off 4 times so had to keep restarting, thought it may have just been a glich so stuck with it for the next two runs, done exactly the same thing!! So off putting, concept is good, shame the app doesn't actually follow suit
Very good so far
Amazingly I completed the 5k👍...and I hate running!
Brilliant. I recommend Jo Whiley!!!!

Finally finished and I feel amazing. Deliberately chose Michael as my coach as he is the only world class runner. The other two are personalities who happen to have taken up running. This app gently introduces you to running with a gentle jog with sound advice on technique. By the end, I could run for 30mins effortlessly.
Very well paced.
Awesomely brilliant.
Great app, easy to use and deifntly helps when starting out as a new jog/runner. Love that it's free too! And you can pick who speaks to you😊 thank you!
Amazing. Really works
A good incentive
App is great would highly recommend
Does what it says on the tin, and it's free

I didn't really believe I was going to make it when I started this app, but now I'm regularly running for thirty minutes and working on getting faster. If you're remotely tempted, give it a go, and select Sarah Millican as your coach.
Brilliant and easy to use
Nice easy steps which ease you into the training. Having the celebs giving words of encouragement is nice but would prefer if they were actually running with me!😁
Fab so far, choosing your mentor is great and make it feel more personal ❤️
It managed to get me runnig so it must be good! I had problems with the trainer as I had to keep resetting them as occasionally came up as unavailable so had to change.
Love the app. Really motivated me to start running. Would love to be able to look back at the stats from my run and see a map of my run.
Just amazing! I never thought I could/would go running, but this app makes it so much more achievable than I could ever have thought. I can't recommend it highly enough.
Easy to use. Helpful motivation to get started. Music plays over the top without interfering with the virtual coach. Happy with it
The structure is good for first time runners but the app closes constantly losing the place you're at during your run.. Really not useful for actually tracking progress

As a 20 stone 5 foot something i was very apprehensive about starting running. First session did hurt a bit but felt brilliant after and it gets easier, I'm really enjoying it now and honestly never thought I would say that
Excellent app unused it when I very first got into running and again when I had to take a break due to an unrelated injury.
Really works
Brilliant, motivating and easy to use
Brilliant
Really good app I would prefer if there was a few more time checks when you're running. The coach you choose doesn't always seem available and its not obvious how to change them.
An excellent app to get you moving. Following a prolonged illness and then a broken leg, my fitness had plummeted. This breaks exercise into manageable and achievable targets. Definitely recommend.
Enjoying it. Doable so far ..just abt to complete first week.
Never run in my life and now jogging slowly for 30 mins nonstop. Unbelievable!
Great app that got us moving during Covid. Half way bell was good for us as our jogs had to be out and back
Excellent app to help motivation and keep me going. Very useful.
Very well designed app that simply works.
Great app , got me running thru a pandemic
Easy to use, enjoying using it
Excellent app and great motivators. Works brilliantly. Highly reommende to those who likeb running.
Super app for coaching a non runner into a runner. Recently improved app since the last time I used it too, v easy to use.
Excellent.

Excellent app. In my 9 th week now. Motivating trainers with simple by effective advice. They come just say the right time to prevent you giving up. A couple of times it didn't have my trainer for the run, but so equally encouraging. Use Strava on the side to record everything. Doing over 6kms at the moment!

Great app to start running from 1 min to 30 mins. Really good plan and nice to have a celeb cheering you on. Had a couple of issues where it kept switching itself off during a run which was frustrating.
Does the job. Finding it quite hard, but it does increase effort at a sensible rate. The app has a problem using the same coach for each run; it forces me to choose a different coach each time.
Breaks you into running, glad i downloaded
Great app!
Great app, gets you running, feels like you have a personal trainer motivating you. It's also free!
If you would of said I could run 5k I would of laughed! But I can now thanks to this ap 🙂🏃‍♀️
Amazing I never thought I would be able to do this but my coach is brillant keeps me motivated. Loving this app
Amazing
Never thought I'd finish, but achieved my goal! This even worked for a 56 year old who has never enjoyed running!
Love this...making my running journey motivational and with a goal I am determined to get there...
Only just started, 3rd run of week one. Good so far
Simple to use, fab motivational chat from Jo Whiley. Great way of getting me back to fitness post covid and Christmas!
Great app helped me immensely. I couldn't run from one lamppost to another when I started. After I finished I was able to take on a fundraiser running 50 miles in the month of January for cancer.
A couch to 10k needs to be created please! The athletes voices is one of the amazing things about it! Currently on week 5. It's simple interface is motivating as well.
It says that the app automatically lowers the volume of your music player but it doesn't work with the radio on my phone when wearing headphones. Otherwise good but I find this really annoying.

Rubbish, finished the run and there is no way to view stats, distance, speed etc. It says couch to 5k but there's no way to check. Of course you could run another app alongside it but after music and this that would be 3 apps running simultaneously, the start running app is well better...sorry Jo
Really helping me to push further
So far so good
Brilliant app - and the Michael Johnson trainer is excellent - definitely recommend
So easy and simple to follow , and a gradual increase, perfect
Easy to use and as a non runner I am amazed that I look forward to doing this.
Never thought i would get anywhere near it!
Slowly building up your stamina
I hadn't run for many years. This app is perfect for easing back in with safe structured sessions.
Excellent
Loving this, on week 4 and running great
Very helpful and Encouraging
Great motivation

Great App to ease me back into running without getting frustrated and there's plenty of help and support groups through the journey to 5k. Even better there's links to music to go with your run from BBC Radio 1
Is helped me change my lifestyle and mindset
Very clear instructions love it.
Fantastic!! I hated running until I used this app!!!
Easy to follow we are doing well. We will do this!
Great for people who want to start their journey with running.
Great app to build yourself up. I've never been able to run but doing it in stages, has made it possible.. .. and I'm even enjoying it !
Great app, really inspiring.
Really helped me get moving!!
Good plan to follow, but have to open and close a few times to get it going each time
Love walking but have never been able to run. This has been brilliant. I'm only on week two bit totally loving it!
Easy to use
It really works. If you are wondering whether to try this out - do it.
The app keeps stopping halfway through the run. The concept though is good
Well structured and a lot of good tips. I've really enjoyed it
All good very helpful
Easy to use

I feel like I'm taking control of my fitness. I've got 1 more run to do in week 2. I'm really enjoying it and I never thought I'd hear myself say that about running. I always thought that running spoiled a good walk. Now, at 66 years old, I'm doing both.
Only problem is phone close and app turns off if you put it in your pocket
Lovin it
61 and up and running again. Thanks Jo Whiley
Fantastic. Really love running now.

Fantastic tool if you are starting (or re-starting like me) running. Eases you into it, gives yoy realistic targets, and encourages all the way through. I am on Wk 5 and what a difference. Had I not had this for encouragement I may have given up by now on my own.
Fun and rewarding
Works for me!
Incredible, loved this app. Really easy to use, can use with strava and music playing. Laura is trainer of choice. Very motivating.

Content is great, I've just completed my second week and I am progressing. However, app not always reliable. Sometimes complains it cant load audio files and has frozen at times. 5 stars for content, 2 for reliability.

I used to absolutely hate running and never thought I would be able to run continuously for more than even 3mins. So delighted I gave this a go! Builds you up really slowly to prevent injury and then before you know it you are fit enough to do the more challenging runs.
Just needed something to get me off my arse and do something positive in the long run it's going to improve my health.
Amazing!
Took me from absolutely no exercise at all to running 5k in 9 weeks. Really enjoyed the app. Highly recommend.

I'm a 31 year old male, who would consider themselves relatively fit. With lockdowns and the cancellation of my hockey which I would normally play twice a week the pounds where starting to be put on, particularly over XMAS. I started using the app at the turn of the year and found the programme an excellent alternative and have since lost 8lbs and am currently running 5k in about 30 minutes.

Keeps crashing but great idea Started ok but since around 15/1/21 the app shuts down sometime in the first 15 minutes. Can leave you warming up for too long or continuing the first run for too long. Only when you notice and restart the app do you find out you're back at the beginning again. Great idea, love Sarah's voice but not much use unless this can be fixed.Now on week 4 and it's do e in twice on two runs. Please fix it. OnePlus6, all up to date

Great app for people like me who always have some reason not to do workouts/walk/run. I started running on my own without any guidance , started feeling dizzy after some time and stopped. now I completed half of my couch5k schedule and didn't feel that I over exerted my self. Workout training pace is perfect for me.

The coaching is amazing, well thought out, and the user interface is very intuitive. 5 stars. The first few times I heard the half time bell I was a bit jarred due to how loud it was, though that's barely an inconvenience for me.
Frustrating - the app is not saving my runs and not letting me progress to later week runs. I only want this app to do one thing and that is play a series of podcasts and it doesn't do that.
Great app. I am currently on week 4 😁
Brilliant got me off the sofa and now running for 5 minutes week 4
Whilst the app is making me get out to run, Jo Whiley's encouragement is great motivation and just what I need each run.

This works brilliantly. If I had one feature request, it would be for the option of a music or podcast mode. At present, the coach talks over the top of whatever is playing in the background, which is fine for music, but frustrating during a podcast - especially if a speaker is in the middle of saying something interesting.
Brilliantly thought through app
Very good App... got me into running 10 years ago and now I am using it with my nephew...
Keeps cutting out half way through . Deleted it and download again but still does the same
Brilliant way to get yourself moving. I chose Jo Whiley as my coach and feel as though she's my new best friend!
Simple, easy, motivational. Could add a distance /route tracker to make it perfect

This is the second time I have used this app. The first time took me from no running to a marathon in good for age time and this time I am recovering from an injury and it is great to curb my enthusiasm so I take my recovery steadily. I think it is great.
Very motivational. Easy to use. I am enjoying it.
Plan is good, but app keeps disconnecting
Great app It's got me going
Although I'm only on week 5, I can't believe how well this works, especially for someone like me who has never run before and doesn't exercise.

I'm now a runner!!! All thanks to Couch to 5k!! I could barely manage 2minutes jogging when I started but now I can do 30mins+, really great for people who want to get into running but don't know where to start 🏃‍♀️
Absolutely 💯 helping my recovery.
Just 1 week in but really motivational and easy to use
Very useful app
I'd never have believed that I could actually run....but I can. Brilliant.
If like me you've never run further than the bus stop in your 46 years then it's hard work to get into the swing of it, but it's great for encouragement and a sense of achievement.
Ive got no complaint so far!! I've just finished week 4 and really enjoying it!

The app closes itself after a short time, so I can't listen to music while using it, I have to keep my phone open and move the timer to where I think it last stopped. Very annoying. It loses my day every time, putting me back to day one.
Really enjoyed using the app. Gave me the confidence to be able to achieve my goal
When the App is working it is fantastic. I've managed to get to wk 3. However keeps crashing and not logging the run.
Works perfectly. I used it a few years ago and did exactly what it said on the tin, and am now having the same experience.
easy to use
Really good way of getting back into exercise
Stopping talking to me halfway through !!
Great app. So far so good.
Tough starting but worth it

Only on my 3rd week . It feels like a sensible , safe , and manageable progression from week to week as long as you remain disciplined . I am 70 , in good health but have never been a runner . I feel optimistic about completing the challenge . I like the fact that you have a choice of " trainer " . Currently I am being urged on by Sanjeev Kohli .
Brilliant app to get you running for the first time

Never been a runner but with no football I was getting fat. Gave this a go and have been so impressed. Incremental increases in difficulty gives a real sense of achievement. Highly recommended. Tom E6

I used to run a lot when I was younger but in very unstructured way. I think couch to 5k is a fantastic app to use to get back to running again or if you're a beginner and never run in your life. It's very well paced.
Great, love that it just pops in during your music to tell you to run or walk, would definitely recommend.
Helped me from running 100 meter and being out of breath to a 5k run
Brilliant app.
Really enjoyed using this app.
Really user friendly and great, once you've enabled the app to work in background
Motivation
Great app for getting you to reach your goal
This is my go-to inspiration for getting moving. It got me running regularly last year and, when I've lost my mojo, it's got me back on track again. I love it!
Living it and loving it
The app has been very helpful and is keeping me on track. I'd give it five stars if the coaches weren't so repetitive. They all sound so bored.

Absolutely can not recommend this enough. Got me running .. iam now doing 8k runs planing on increasing as weeks go on... 8 weeks ago I struggled to even run 1 minute .. love it . Love you for creating this app . Thank you
Use strava along side to track distance. Helped alot.
I like that even without data, it works👏🏿👏🏿. Very very good app
The app is great and I love having Jo Wiley chat me through!
Great encouragement and enjoying the running experience.
If it wasn't for this app talking me through I 100% wouldn't have completed my 1st run let alone carry on

It's changed. I used it last year and it was brilliant but now it stops during the warm up walk and I end up walking for longer before I realise. Then I have to restart the app, find my place and start again, only for it to repeat. I would love to keep using it as I found it to be really beneficial for me.
Very simple to use and the program builds up slowly and easily. I am in my 60's and haven't run for over 30 years but have not had a problem in managing the sessions.
This is a fantastic experience,THANK YOU SO MUCH!!! I am only on week 4 but I love it and cannot wait for each run day to begin.
Only two weeks in but already feeling much better. As someone who hasn't done much exercise for years, I wasn't sure it would be sufficiently motivating but it's a great reintroduction.
It is a good coaching app for those starting out with running.
Fab app, I have never enjoyed running and never got into it but have always wanted to for the benefits. This app has helped me to enjoy it and gain my fitness levels
Great plan but shocking how much it crashes in the middle of runs. Will delete and try and find a better app that actually works.

This is just really good and effective and helpful. Shame it doesn't have like a persistent notification thing, so you can switch out in the walk periods, but that's really the worst thing I can think.

Excellent, basic, but with annoying flaws. I recommend this, but it is so annoying when the app tells you a run is complete, but all record of it is then lost as you haven't manually saved it. Then having reminder alarms to run going off while you're running is just silly. Five starts with a bit more thought in usability.
Love it! I don't have to think about the process I just follow Michael Jordan 👌🙏🏼

Nothing happens when I hit Go. Sometimes the timer will count down but no audio. Tried shutting all other apps down, reset app, restarted phone. Very glitchy! Something must be up as it's worked on my phone before.
Great! The app works as expected. The app runs over the music of your choice, dimming the volume temporarily when your chosen instructor gives you directions.

Struggled to run for 60 seconds at a time at the start, completed the program this morning with a 5.5mile run. The app could be improved by having a different voice over for each run rather than same one for the full week and some runs wouldn't allow my chosen person so had to change a few times but on the whole these are minor grumbles.
So easy and refreshing

Amazing. I won't lie it is hard work at first. I stuck at it and now can run for 30 minutes non stop. I may not be the fastest runner out there but actually now enjoy getting out of the house and burning some calories. I chose Micheal Johnson as my coach. Very motivating!

Just finished my last run on week 9!! Feeling fantastic, don't think I could have done it without some banging tunes and the encouraging and relaxing voice of Micheal Johnson. I feel like he has been there every step of my running (plodding!) journey with just the right amount of information during each run. Thank you 💗 Kate

It's easy to set up your aims and choosing the coach to suit you is great. I've not ran/ jogged for over 30 years and am at least 4 stone overweight but I've found it really great to do. The targets are reachable and although I've felt like crying at the end of some runs, when I've done the cool down walk, I feel fab and really pleased with myself for being able to do it.I've got Sarah Millican as my coach and she's great. The only downside is I can't hear her over my music so I run without it
Easy app to use .... very clear instructions and lots if motivational comments. Great for anyone wanting to try running firvthe first time.

Great app. Well laid out. Different choice of voice instructors. Can play your music same time and sound reduces when the instructor needs to talk. Length of time running gradually increases over the weeks. I couldnt run without a bottle of water before and always used to stop to walk. And now I can run (jog) 30 minutes without water. Very happy. Seriously worth a try
Really good app, builds you up gradually to reach your goal
Really hard but with persistence I know I can do this thank you
So far so good! Run 4 of 27 and loving the support ❤
Really enjoy this app! Jo wiley is a great motivation
Brilliant. Nice and gentle
So easy to use
Good but cant get music to play , help!!@🤣

Good feeling to tick every run off...however I ran listening to the podcast...I found Laura motivating. Feeling much better, lighter in weight...C25k is a good way to get back on track with running or to start if you've never run before.
Brilliant easy to use and follow, gradually builds up stamina and distance.
Great app. Some issues with stopping if using multiple apps at the same time (i.e. watching Netflix whilst running!) otherwise would have been 5 stars.
I like it & it's helping me jog/run. And it's building my statmina
Just started but enjoyed week 1
Easy to use, helpful reminders

Really enjoying this. Couches give helpful advice and app is easy to use. Great to see my progress. Just remember to allow the app to continue running in the background as the default is to shut off if screen is locked.
Excellent motivational app which builds up you running gradually and tells you exactly what to do.
Genuinely the first thing that made me feel like running for fun.

Not a runner at all but managed to do the full programme. 5k seems to be a loose calculation on the amount of time you've run not actual distance run so better using a running app to make sure you're actually doing the 5k if that's what you want to achieve.
It has been a great introduction into the scary world of jogging. Laura is great at talking you through.
Really good if you stick with it not long completed this couldn't recommend it enough. 👍
So easy to follow and don't feel too bad 2 weeks in!
Motivational
Perfect for sloths like me who are full of excuses why they don't move. Now I can run for 40 minutes. 😅
For a beginner I think is great as you start off slow and build up as the weeks go on.
Great motivation
Really works. Week 4 I'm starting to realise I can do this. Lots of help with technique, stretching and music as well 👍🏻
Really good to help develop fitness.
Miracle, just completed the 9 weeks and wow I did it, could not have done without the app, Jo Whiley was a great choice supported me all the way. I'm a runner now

I am on week 4 and I am really enjoying it so far! Looking forward to being able to run 5k at the end!
Easy to use total sucess
I absolutely love this app! From literally a couch potato to running almost 5k!

This app is really helping me to start running, i have to turn ny battery saver on my Huwawei off or it closes the app in the background but other rhan that it works great with spotify in the background too. Would highly reccommend to anyone who wants to start running.
So far so good, helping me improve my fitness

The concept is good, but the app itself is fairly poorly written and has multiple issues. It loses the coach audio causing you to reset it. It has bugs that causes it to lose focus and thus lose the audio mid run. It has crashed a couple of times and has also stated that it needs more storage (100mb) when over 100 GB is free on both SD card and internal storage. The actual couch 2 5KM is an excellent approach and am really enjoying it. The app whilst bug ridden is usable on a run by run basis
This really motivated to get to my 5km goal. Love the way each week is broken up into the different runs to build your stamina up.
Must admit not an easy task, but made much easier with a friendly trainer with you along the way for motivation. An excellent training tool for beginners
Having Navid (Sanjeev Kohli) from still game walk me through the steps is fantastic, its helping me run further with greater ease. All you have to to do is stick with it.
Absolutely fabulous thankyou 7 weeks 4 days x
Great motivator. Love Jo Whiley's voice
I am enjoying it. It seems to be we'll planned

Great motivation to keep going. Don't think I would have completed all these runs with out Jo Whiley in my ear. I enjoyed it and remained injury free. If you are thinking about it... Give it a go. Nothing to loose.
Brilliant. Has made me enjoy running for the 1st time ever at 45.
Absolutely loving it. Just the right amount of easing in with pushing back. I'd probably do anything Jo Whiley asked me to do anyway.
Really great app to get you going. Just listen to the instruction and stick to it and you'll be there in the time frame/schedule. Brilliant
I signed up for a challenge and I needed something to help with the training as I haven't ran for a lot of years. This was exactly what I needed. I would recommend to everyone.

For me this has been the only pain-free way to get fitter. It is very accessible. When I fall out of the habit of regular exercise, I use C25K to get back into it. As a non-sporty person, C25K has given me confidence that I can set and achieve fitness goals.
Amazing i run straugh 5ks now wothout a worry
There's good points to this app - the timer page and run breakdowns, but it often seems to not work smoothly and almost every time I have to change my trainer selection for some reason!
Was great and motivational to hedge the voice. Would be even better if it tracked your distance or route.
Brilliant app
This app is amazing. I went from barely being able to run for 1min to running for 30mins+. Highly recommend.
Only on run 2 but feel the app is really good. The celebrities are supportive at coaching you through the runs!
Fantastic app really helped me learn to run for the first time in 14years. Would highly recommend for anyone considering it
Brilliant never thought I could do it 😁 I feel so happy that I have completed it. I am happier and healthier and really enjoy it, when its finished 🤣🏃‍♀️
Well led course allowing progress at your own pace. Variety of guide voices to choose from but sometimes you are forced to swap
Loving it, gradually building up my stamina is working
Gave me the motivation to exercise and complete the 9 weeks program. Also liked the way it encouraged you throughout each run especially near the end of the program when the runs were longer
Great app
Perfect for beginners or those wanting to rekindle their long lost love of running.

For my personal liking this is one of the most beneficial apps I have come across, thank to this app I am a regular runner now and I am liking if not loving running The app itself however is very basic (perhaps that's why i loved it so much), the app helped me to love running instead of giving up after 2 weeks of struggle (like i did in the past) I can only recommend 👌 fab app
Downloaded on to a Huawei & it doesn't work during workouts when background closes, you have to keep opening & fast forwarding it to continue the workout or you could be running/walking for hours.
Although I couldnt get Jo Whiley, as didnt have sufficient data? I have found the app easy and motivational. I also listen to bbc sounds pace setter rap so more rhythmic!
I can run for 30 mins! Great app great program!!
Really useful tool, great development week on week. Sarah is a great coach. She keeps me going.
Think it's great lots of encouragement and it's a great way of keeping fit, meeting people and achieving your goals

Brilliant app, I'm not a strong runner so started couch to 5K to set myself a challenge and I am amazed at how far I have come from struggling in week 1 not able to run for more than a couple of minutes to now running for 30 minutes without stopping, I recommend it to everybody who wants to improve their fitness and have been recommending it to all my family and friends!
Easy to use app. Having Sarah in my ear encourages me to get through the run. The gradual progression works well for my level of fitness.

Great. Love the app. Very clear UI, easy to use and very happy with Jo as my trainer. For a DJ she has an uncanny habit of crashing the break thoug. But I guess I can't blame her for that - it's not her hand on the needle. 😁
Want to get fit
I am amazed at how I have come on in only a few days

It certainly got me up to 5k so it can be done! It wasn't easy in parts and some days went better than others but keep going and you'll get there and achieve your goal of running 5k and looking like a red sweaty mess.

Really motivational. Music tracks great and i love how the sound adapts to when the talking starts.
